gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 119, Nuggets 93
gameRecap.excerpt: The Thunder defeated the Nuggets, 119-93. Shai Gilgeous-Alexander led Oklahoma City with his fifth 40-point game of the year (40 points, four rebounds, three assists) as Chet Holmgren added 24 points (9-14 FG, 4-4 3PT), six rebounds, and two blocks. Nikola Jokic led Denver with 19 points, 10 rebounds, and seven assists. The Thunder have now won three in a row and improve to 21-9 on year while this loss snaps a 6-game win streak for Denver, as they move to 23-11 on the year.
